            print('empty')
            return

        curr = self.head

            store += str(curr.val) + ' '
            curr = curr.next
        store += str(curr.val)
        print(store)
        return

def delete_by_loop(self, val):
        if self.head is None:
            return
        if self.head.val == val:
            del_node = self.head
            self.head = self.head.next
            print(del_node.val)
            return

        prev = self.head
        curr = None

        while prev.next is not None:
            curr = prev.next
            if curr.val == val:
                prev.next = curr.next
                return
            prev = curr
        return
